<div class="row-fluid">
  <div class="span6">
    Parameters to use:
    <ul>
      <li>first_name</li>
      <li>last_name</li>
      <li>company</li>
      <li>door</li>
    </ul>
    <P>All matches are case insensitive and partial matches are accepted by default (for example, "first_name=geoff" will match to the first name "Geoffrey"). Doors in Galvanize include the Front, Atrium, Back, and Knoll doors.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="span6">
    For example, try:
    <ul>
      <li>first_name=geoff AND last_name=schorkopf</li>
      <li>last_name=casimir OR company=gschool</li>
      <li>door=atrium AND company=roximity</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This language is meant to be flexible. Adding the operator "OR" will match anything on both sides of the conjunction. Adding the operator "AND" will only return matches for both sides of the conjunction.</P>
    <p>Note: "AND" and "OR" are case sensitive.</P>
  </div>
</div>